HEADWORD: Osmazome
<hw>Os"ma*zome</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ smell,
odor + <?/ broth: cf. F. <ets>osmaz⟦ocir⟧me</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Old
Chem.)</fld> <def>A substance formerly supposed to give to soup and
broth their characteristic odor, and probably consisting of one or
several of the class of nitrogenous substances which are called
<xex>extractives</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Osmiamate</ent>⟦br⟧
